---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Fesal Fayed" description="Who Fesal Fayed is: ML engineer in Miami, FIU Data Science & AI, fine-tuner of open models, builder of agentic infrastructure.">
  <article class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Fesal. I live in Miami and I build machine-learning systems that do
      work — not demos, not decks. The through-line in everything below is the
      same: take a model, wire it into real infrastructure with real data, and
      make it operate.
    </p>

    <p>
      I studied Data Science &amp; Artificial Intelligence at Florida
      International University. Somewhere along the way the interesting part of
      ML stopped being the model and became the <em>system around the model</em>:
      the data pipelines feeding it, the tool interfaces it acts through, the
      guardrails that let it run unattended. That's the lane I work in.
    </p>

    <p>
      Concretely, right now that means three things. I fine-tune open models for
      agentic tool use — my <a href="/blog/gpt-oss-20b-tool-finetune/">gpt-oss-20b
      tool-calling family</a> ships in four formats and has crossed 9k+ downloads
      on Hugging Face. I run a personal-data pipeline (<em>qs</em>) that pulls my
      biometrics, phone context, training and journal data into one schema —
      substrate for models that predict my own behavior. And I operate a small
      fleet of AI agents that manage my infrastructure: they deploy sites, run
      research pipelines, watch cron jobs, and file their own work logs on a
      kanban queue.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm also co-founder of a company still in stealth — vertical intelligence
      for high-margin local operators. More on that when it's ready.
    </p>

    <p>
      I write <a href="/blog/">build logs and dissections</a> of these systems.
      House rules: the result comes first, the things that didn't work get their
      own section, and claims come with references. If a post reads like
      marketing, I've failed.
    </p>

    <p>
      Talk to me: <a href="mailto:hi@fesalfayed.com">hi@fesalfayed.com</a> ·
      <a href="https://github.com/fesalfayed">GitHub</a> ·
      <a href="https://huggingface.co/fesalfayed">Hugging Face</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { max-width: var(--measure); margin: 0 auto; padding-top: 2rem; }
  .about h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
  .about p { margin: 1rem 0; color: var(--fg-soft); }
  .about p:first-of-type { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--fg); }
</style>
